=============================

h-screen :

1.Fits screen perfectly.
2.Container stays fixed, content overflows.
3.height: 100vh;

=============================

min-h-screen :
1.Fits screen perfectly.
2.Container expands to fit content.
3.min-height: 100vh;

=============================

py : add top bottom pading.
px : add right left padding.
pt : add top padding.
pb : add bottom padding.

=============================

my : add top bottom margin.
mx : add right left margin.
mt : add top margin.
mb : add bottom margin.

=============================
Sizes : 
Prefix ||	Minimum Width || 	Typical Device
-	     || 0px	          ||  Mobile phones (base styles).
sm:	   || 640px	        ||  Large phones / Small tablets.
md:	   || 768px	        ||  Tablets (like an iPad).
lg:	   || 1024px	      ||  Laptops and small desktops.
xl:	   || 1280px	      ||  Large Desktop monitors.
2xl:   || 1536px	      ||  Ultra-wide monitors.

=============================

m-auto : Centers a fixed-width element horizontally.

items-center: Centers items vertically inside a flex container.

justify-between: Pushes items to the far edges (perfect for navbars).

gap-4: Adds consistent spacing between items in a flex or grid (no more manual margins!).

grid-cols-2: Instantly creates a 2-column layout.

rounded-lg / rounded-full: Rounds the corners (pill-shaped if full).

shadow-md / shadow-xl: Adds depth with a drop shadow.

border / border-gray-200: Adds a subtle 1px border.

bg-opacity-50: Makes a background semi-transparent.

backdrop-blur-sm: Creates that "frosted glass" effect (great for fixed headers).

truncate: Cuts off long text with an ellipsis (...) so it doesn't break your layout.

inset-0: A shortcut for top: 0; right: 0; bottom: 0; left: 0; (perfect for overlays).

=============================

